# Project documentation — mandatory reference

All product, UX, escrow-role, state-machine, and MVP-scope decisions **must** come from the files in `docs/`. Do not invent flows, screens, roles, fields, or acceptance criteria that contradict or extend beyond these documents without explicit user approval.

External Trustless Work platform docs ([docs.trustlesswork.com](https://docs.trustlesswork.com/trustless-work)) cover SDK/API mechanics; **this repo’s `docs/`** cover what this template builds and how users move through it.

---

## Document index

| File | Purpose | Read when |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `docs/PRODUCT-BRIEF.md` | One-liner, problem, parties, core flow, MVP scope, example milestones | Orienting on the product; quick scope checks; explaining the template |

**Precedence when docs overlap:** `PRODUCT-BRIEF.md` is the executive summary—if it conflicts with the PRD or flow doc, follow the PRD/flow doc and flag the inconsistency to the user.

