## Combining with other project rules

- **Architecture / forms / folders:** Follow `.cursor/rules/DAPP.mdc`, `FORMS.mdc`, and `FOLDER_LAYOUT.mdc` for *how* to build; **`docs/`** defines *what* to build.
- **Trustless Work SDK / blocks:** Use `.agents/skills/trustless-work/` and platform docs for *integration mechanics*; **`docs/`** defines template-specific roles, flows, and UI expectations.
- **Conflict:** `docs/` wins on product behavior; code patterns win on structure/style. Escalate unresolved product conflicts to the user.

---

## When the user asks a product question

Answer from `docs/` first. Cite the doc file and section (e.g. “PRD §9.4”, “Flow doc Flow C”). If the docs are silent, say so and propose options aligned with MVP non-goals and open questions (PRD §19)—do not present guesses as requirements.
